    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You have learned the value of always knowing how to, and when to escape or run. You practice your escape routes the night before and in your dreams in order to avoid wasting time. When you would take the dash action, you instead are able to increase your movement speed by twice your base speed. Once you do this, you cannot gain the benefit of this pattern again until you choose to reduce your speed to 0 at the beginning of your turn or finish a rest.</p>",
